    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 NVIDIA's GR00T Is Going Commercial (And N2 Is Already Casting Shadows)\n\nNational Robotics Week came with a hardware announcement, a software announcement, and a veiled reminder to every humanoid robot company not already inside NVIDIA's ecosystem.\n\n- **GR00T N1.7:** Now in early access with a commercial license — generalized robot skills including advanced dexterous control, ready for production deployments. Manufacturers can actually buy it now.\n- **GR00T N2 teased:** Based on NVIDIA's DreamZero research, it uses a \"World Action Model\" architecture. NVIDIA says robots with N2 will complete unfamiliar tasks at 2x+ the frequency of leading visual-language-action models. (NVIDIA's benchmarks. Apply appropriate seasoning.)\n\n*Robots that handle \"unfamiliar environments\" at double the frequency of competitors, announced during National Robotics Week. Jensen Huang has always had flair.*\n\n**Sources:** [NVIDIA Newsroom](https://nvidianews.nvidia.com/news/nvidia-releases-new-physical-ai-models-as-global-partners-unveil-next-generation-robots) | [NVIDIA Blog](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/national-robotics-week-2026/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Yann LeCun Raised $1 Billion to Prove ChatGPT Is Wrong\n\nAfter years of publicly arguing that large language models are \"a dead end,\" LeCun left Meta, founded AMI Labs, and raised $1.03B in seed funding — the largest seed round in European history.\n\n- **The bet:** AMI is building \"world models\" based on LeCun's Joint Embedding Predictive Architecture (JEPA) — AI that learns by understanding how the physical world works, not by predicting the next token. Target applications: robotics, drones, healthcare, manufacturing.\n- **The investors:** Cathay Innovation, Bezos Expeditions, Mark Cuban, Eric Schmidt, and Tim Berners-Lee backed the round. When the inventor of the internet funds your AI startup, that's either very validating or a sign of timeline anxiety.\n\n*LeCun spent years saying LLMs can't reason about the physical world. He now has $1 billion to prove it. The LLM companies have already moved on to robotics. Cool, great.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/09/yann-lecuns-ami-labs-raises-1-03-billion-to-build-world-models/) | [SiliconAngle](https://siliconangle.com/2026/03/10/yann-lecuns-new-startup-ami-labs-raises-1-03b-train-world-models/)\n\n---\n\n## 🪟 Microsoft Has Three New AI Models and None of Them Are Named GPT\n\nMicrosoft released MAI-Transcribe-1, MAI-Voice-1, and MAI-Image-2 — its own foundational models, built in-house, no OpenAI involved.\n\n- **What they do:** MAI-Transcribe-1 does speech-to-text 2.5x faster than Azure's existing offering. MAI-Voice-1 generates 60 seconds of audio in one second. MAI-Image-2 debuted top 3 on Arena.ai's leaderboard with 2x faster generation on Copilot.\n- **What it means:** Microsoft has spent $13B+ making OpenAI's models its products. It is now shipping its own models that compete with OpenAI's in the same domains. This is either \"portfolio diversification\" or \"hedging while your partner races toward AGI.\"\n\n*Microsoft built products on OpenAI for four years and then built products that replace them. No notes.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/02/microsoft-takes-on-ai-rivals-with-three-new-foundational-models/) | [VentureBeat](https://venturebeat.com/technology/microsoft-launches-3-new-ai-models-in-direct-shot-at-openai-and-google)\n\n---\n\n## 🏆 Gemini 3.1 Is Leading the Benchmarks. Claude Mythos Was Leaked.\n\nThe April 2026 model race has a new benchmark leader and a rumored entrant — neither of which are from OpenAI.\n\n- **Gemini 3.1 Pro:** Currently leads 13 of 16 major benchmarks, according to aggregator data. Google quietly took the top of the leaderboard while the industry was watching the GPT-5.4/5.5 succession drama.\n- **Claude Mythos:** An Anthropic model positioned above Opus was apparently leaked — reportedly the next-generation flagship above Claude Opus. No confirmed release date, but existence in the pipeline is established. Anthropic's naming conventions have always carried dramatic energy.\n\n*Everyone was watching OpenAI drop 5.4 and bake 5.5. Meanwhile Google quietly took 13 benchmarks. Classic misdirection.*\n\n**Sources:** [RenovateQR AI Models April 2026](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-models-april-2026) | [Crescendo AI](https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-ai-news-and-updates)"
